de.esoco.lib.expression

Interface BinaryPredicate.ThrowingBinaryPredicate<L,R,E extends java.lang.Exception>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BinaryFunction<L,R,java.lang.Boolean>, BinaryPredicate<L,R>, java.util.function.Function<L,java.lang.Boolean>, java.util.function.Predicate<L>
    Enclosing interface:
    BinaryPredicate<L,R>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface BinaryPredicate.ThrowingBinaryPredicate<L,R,E extends java.lang.Exception>
extends BinaryPredicate<L,R>
    A sub-interface that allows implementations to throw checked exceptions. If an exception occurs it will be converted into a runtime exception of the type FunctionException.
